-- Sartorius Raises 2010 Forecast `Slightly' as Nine-Month Profit Increases
-- B y   T o m   L a v e l l
-- 2010-10-22T04:38:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-22/sartorius-raises-2010-forecast-slightly-as-nine-month-profit-increases.html
Sartorius AG raised its full-year
profitability forecast “slightly,” predicting earnings before
interest, taxes and amortization as a proportion of sales will
rise by 2.5 percentage points from an earlier outlook of a 1 to
2 percentage-point margin gain, the company said today in a
statement.  Nine-month net income, excluding non-cash amortization and
one-time expenses, rose to 26.4 million euros, or 1.55 euros a
share, from 13.9 million euros. or 81 cents, a year earlier, the
company said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tom Lavell at 
 tlavell@bloomberg.net  